com.vectorprint.configuration.parser

Class ParameterizableParserImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vectorprint.configuration.binding.parameters.AbstractParameterizableBinding<List<String>>
      • com.vectorprint.configuration.parser.ParameterizableParserImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ParameterizableParser<List<String>>, ParameterizableSerializer, ParameterizableParserImplConstants

    public class ParameterizableParserImpl
extends AbstractParameterizableBinding<List<String>>
implements ParameterizableParserImplConstants
    A parser for Parameterizable objects and / or Configurable in the form class(param1=v1|v2,param2=v3) separators ("," or ")") can be escaped, example configuration: 
    
         Shape(bordercolor=#663322,color=#11aa55,borderwidth=2,SHAPE=bezier,fill=true,background=false,points=60|20|90|20|75|40,close=false)
 
    
 Annotations will be processed, SettingsAnnotationProcessor.initSettings(Object,EnhancedMap) will be called on the class.
 Parameterizables and Parameters will be initialized and default values for parameters will initialized from settings, see
 ParameterHelper.findKey(java.lang.String, java.lang.Class, com.vectorprint.configuration.EnhancedMap, com.vectorprint.configuration.binding.parameters.ParameterHelper.SUFFIX)

      • parseParameterizable

        public Parameterizable parseParameterizable()
        Description copied from interface: ParameterizableParser
        Suggestion for how a parser could initialize a Parameterizable (in this order):
        • extend AbstractParameterizableParser
        • SettingsAnnotationProcessor.initSettings(java.lang.Object, com.vectorprint.configuration.EnhancedMap) on the Parameterizable class
        • create an instance of the Parameterizable class
        • call ParameterizableParser.initParameterizable(com.vectorprint.configuration.parameters.Parameterizable) on the abstract
        • call ParameterizableParser.initParameter(com.vectorprint.configuration.parameters.Parameter, java.lang.Object) for each parameter found. In this method you can call ParamBindingHelper.setValueOrDefault(com.vectorprint.configuration.parameters.Parameter, java.io.Serializable, boolean) after turning the Object into the type needed by the Parameter.
        • finally you may want to set (default) values for parameters using ParameterHelper.findKey(java.lang.String, java.lang.Class, com.vectorprint.configuration.EnhancedMap, com.vectorprint.configuration.binding.parameters.ParameterHelper.SUFFIX), ParameterizableParser.parseAsParameterValue(java.lang.String, com.vectorprint.configuration.parameters.Parameter) and ParamBindingHelper.setValueOrDefault(com.vectorprint.configuration.parameters.Parameter, java.io.Serializable, boolean).
        Specified by:
        parseParameterizable in interface ParameterizableParser<List<String>>
        Returns:
